p: Sterols represented the 8.37% of the extract and included fucosterol and cholesterol in a percentage of 7.40% and 0.97%, respectively ( Table 1). We also calculated the ratio between fucosterol and cholesterol (F:C) which corresponded to 7.6:1. Other noteworthy compounds identified were: α- and δ-tocopherol, which corresponded to 0.17 and 0.19% respectively, phytol (5.27%), neophytadiene, a terpene compound that amounted to 5.56%, 2,4-di- tert-butylphenol (0.18%) and dihydroactinidiolide (0.37%) ( Table 1).
